  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Project Manager",
  "description": "<h3>We’re looking\nfor an experienced Project Manager to lead\ntransformer field projects from planning to commissioning. If you have a strong\nbackground in power or distribution transformers and enjoy managing site-based\nelectrical projects, we’d love to hear from you.</h3><h3>Key\nResponsibilities</h3><p>·        \nPlan, execute, and manage transformer-related\nprojects (installation, repair, testing, refurbishment, and commissioning).</p><p>·        \nCoordinate field activities involving power\ntransformers, substations, and associated equipment.</p><p>·        \nManage project schedules, budgets, resources,\nand risk mitigation plans.</p><p>·        \nLiaise with clients, utilities, consultants,\nvendors, and internal teams to ensure smooth project execution.</p><p>·        \nOversee site activities, ensuring compliance\nwith safety standards, quality requirements, and project specifications.</p><p>·        \nReview technical drawings, specifications,\nmethod statements, and test reports related to transformers.</p><p>·        \nMonitor contractor performance and ensure\nadherence to scope, timelines, and contractual obligations.</p><p>·        \nPrepare progress reports, project documentation,\nand final handover packages.</p><p>·        \nIdentify and resolve technical and operational\nissues during project execution.</p><p>·        \nEnsure compliance with applicable standards\n(IEC, IEEE, ANSI, local utility standards).</p><h3>            Qualifications\n& Experience</h3><ul><li>Degree in Electrical Engineering (or related)</li><li>Minimum 3 years years\n     of project management experience in the transformer or power sector with\n     Electrical background.</li><li>Strong knowledge of power and distribution\n     transformers, substations, and field operations</li><li>Able to assist with project management\n     tools and methodologies, technical documentation, and site activities</li><li>Self-motivated and able to work\n     independently with minimal supervision</li><li>Able to communicate and prepare basic\n     reports in <strong>Mandarin</strong></li><li>Strong leadership, coordinating with\n     internal teams, contractors, and stakeholders</li><li>Willingness to travel to project sites.<strong>\n     </strong></li></ul><p><strong>How to Apply:</strong><br />\nPlease submit your CV and relevant project experience to info@sgbsin.com.sg / nancy@sgbsin.com.sg</p>",
  "minimumYearsExperience": 2,
